The Washington and Gateshead South parliamentary constituency is located in the North East of England.
It was created as a result of the 2023 periodic review of Westminster constituencies and first contested in the 2024 general election,
The constituency includes parts of the Metropolitan Borough of Gateshead (Birtley and Lamesley wards) and the City of Sunderland (Castle, Redhill, Washington Central, Washington East, Washington North, Washington South, and Washington West wards)
Our current Chairman is Paul Donaghy
( Our local candidate for the 2024 General election, Regional mayoral candidate and former Washington South Counciillor )
" We are committed to making a difference both locally and Nationally,
Reform Councillors, Candidates & volunteers work in the community for the community, We work for a better future for everyone.
I invite you to join us in this mission and join the movement to reform politics for good
Your local Reform UK team come from all backgrounds, everyone who wants to fight for a better, fairer future is welcomed."
Paul Donaghy
